<br>
This is really the essential point. Cleric nukes seem to have just been put there as way to thumb thier noses at wizards. Incidentally, the other day I had the luxury of being in a group with a nuking cleric who was out-critting 900 to 1200. <br>
<br>
Why do clerics even SCF? If you took it away from them, capped thier nukes at, say 40, clerics would be needed just as much as they are today. The point isnt that clerics are more efficient nukers than wizards--they aren't. But they come too close, at too many levels to being able to nuke for as much. <br>
<br>
Wzard nuking doesnt  really start to seperate from the pack until 49plus., Cleric healing begins to dust other healers around 35 or so. I just want more distance in offensive magic, and I would like it to occur earlier. DOn't want to strip clercis of thier nukes? Fine. Cap them somewhere before 50.<br>
<br>
